PR DESCRIPTION:
<!--
If this is your first time contributing to the project, please consider reviewing https://github.com/hibernate/hibernate-orm/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md
-->

This PR introduces a new annotation `@NaturalIdConstraint` which allows explicitly specifying the name of the unique constraint generated for an entity `@NaturalId`.

Currently, Hibernate generates the name of the unique constraint enforcing a natural id using the configured implicit naming strategy. This makes it difficult for users to control the generated constraint name, which can be important for database schema naming conventions or migration tools.

The new annotation allows defining the constraint name at the entity level.

Example usage:

```java
@Entity
@NaturalIdConstraint(name = "PERSON_SSN")
class Person {

    @Id
    Long id;

    @NaturalId
    String ssn;
}
```
