POINTS:
- [hibernate-core/src/test/java/org/hibernate/orm/test/locking/LockingAndDeletingInDifferentThreadsTest.java:32] ```suggestion
@RequiresDialectFeature(feature = DialectFeatureChecks.SupportsConcurrentTransactions.class)
public class LockingAndDeletingInDifferentThreadsTest {
```
- [hibernate-core/src/test/java/org/hibernate/orm/test/locking/SelectLockingInDifferentThreadsTest.java:116] I'm not sure what exact interleaving you want to test, but it might be easier to do this to consistently test a specific scenario without threads.

```suggestion
		scope.inTransaction(
				session -> {
					Parent parent = new Parent( 1L, "parent" );
					parent.addChild( new Child( 4L, "child1" ) );
					session.persist( parent );

					Parent parent2 = new Parent( 2L, "parent2" );
					parent2.addChild( new Child( 5L, "child2" ) );
					session.persist( parent2 );
				}
		);
		scope.inTransaction(
				session1 -> {
					Parent parent1 = session1.find( Parent.class, 1L, LockModeType.PESSIMISTIC_WRITE );
					scope.inTransaction(
							session2 -> {
								Parent parent2 = session2.find( Parent.class, 2L, LockModeType.PESSIMISTIC_WRITE );
								session2.remove( parent2 );
							}
					);
					session1.remove( parent1 );
				}
		);
	}
```
- [hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/sql/exec/spi/JdbcSelectWithActionsBuilder.java:29] How about creating a `LoadedValuesCollectorFactory` class that eagerly computes the `Set<NavigablePath>` but then creates a `LoadedValuesCollector` with just the two collections `List<LoadedEntityRegistration> entitiesToLock` and `List<LoadedCollectionRegistration> collectionsToLock`.
Seems that would also reduce some code duplication.

